		<div id="page-container" class="left with-sidebar" tabindex="-1">
							
							
									<h1 id="page-title" class="page-title">Category: For Advisors&#8217; Information</h1>
				
													
						
		

				
			<div id="post-3765" class="post-3765 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-advising-weekly-updates category-for-advisors-information category-professional-development">

                                <div class="postmetadata">
					<span class="meta-date"><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-development-banner-9-upgrade-info-and-advice-for-users-to-prepare-for-october-14th-go-live/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Banner 9 Upgrade &#8211; info and advice for users to prepare for October 14th go live." rel="bookmark">
						<span class="month">Sep</span>
						<span class="day">09</span>
						<span class="year">2018</span>
					</a></span>


					

					<span class="meta-author"><span>by jvolpe</span></span>

				</div>
                
				<div class="post-contents">
										<h3 class="entry-title">
					<a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-development-banner-9-upgrade-info-and-advice-for-users-to-prepare-for-october-14th-go-live/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Banner 9 Upgrade &#8211; info and advice for users to prepare for October 14th go live." rel="bookmark">PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Banner 9 Upgrade &#8211; info and advice for users to prepare for October 14th go live.</a>
					</h3>
                    					    <div class="post-category">Posted in <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/advising-weekly-updates/">Advising Weekly Updates</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/for-advisors-information/">For Advisors' Information</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/professional-development/">Professional Development</a></div>
                    					<div class="post-content">
					<p>As you are probably aware Banner 9 is being implemented on October 14, because vendor support for Oracle forms (current Banner 8 infrastructure) will be discontinued this coming December. The Office of Student Systems Services (OSSS) in conjunction with other offices within Academic and Enrollment Services are preparing for this upgrade.</p>
<p>You will be receiving a series of emails over the next couple of weeks about preparing for this upgrade.  Banner 9 look and feel is different and there are some navigation and form changes.</p>
<p><strong>What are we doing to help with this transition?</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>The OSSS website (<a href="https://osss.uic.edu/">osss.uic.edu</a>) has been updated to include Banner 9 information. There are documents for the various college and department processes. The documentation will be completed by September 14.</li>
<li>Training will be conducted for the following areas:
<ol>
<li><em>Schedule Planners:</em> Beginning in September there will be training for all of the schedule planners.  Sign up will start on September 14 through the OSSS website.</li>
<li><em>SZACURU:</em> College staff who make curriculum changes will have a training/overview session(s) after the October 14th go live.  Sign up will be late September through the OSSS website.</li>
<li><em>Graduation Processing:</em> College staff who process graduation applications for students will be offered training/overview sessions in November. An email to sign up through the OSSS website will be sent mid-late October.</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>What do you need to do this week to prepare for Banner 9?</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Start by reviewing the information on the OSSS website. Especially look at the navigation components. View the AITS Navigational Video. The URL is &#8211; <a href="https://www.aits.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=558&amp;pageId=941936">https://www.aits.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=558&amp;pageId=941936</a> .</li>
<li>AITS is doing a Banner Student overview session on September 27. The sign-up link is on this page <a href="https://emails.illinois.edu/newsletter/182706.html">https://emails.illinois.edu/newsletter/182706.html</a> .</li>
<li>Log into the Banner 9 playground that AITS has set up. The URL is <a href="https://www.aits.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=558&amp;pageId=941949">https://www.aits.uillinois.edu/cms/One.aspx?portalId=558&amp;pageId=941949</a></li>
<li>You should begin now to practice the navigation functions. Enter in the page that you normally access.  Enter in the required information and always click on Go.  In the left hand sidebar there are various icons.  Click on the icons to see how to navigate through Banner. Navigate to another page that you normally access by using the sidebar.</li>
</ol>
<p>OSSS will be sending email each week with advice to help you prepare for Banner 9.  You should spend at least an hour per week learning about Banner to prepare for the <strong>October 14</strong> go live date.</p>
<p>Please let me know if there are any questions.</p>
<p>Thanks!</p>
<p>Mike Kamowski<br />
Executive Director<br />
Office of Student Systems Services<br />
<a href="mailto:mikek@uic.edu">mikek@uic.edu</a></p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<br class="clear" />

			</div><!-- end div post -->

		
			<div id="post-3757" class="post-3757 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-advising-weekly-updates category-for-advisors-information">

                                <div class="postmetadata">
					<span class="meta-date"><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/for-advisors-info-las-fall-2018-sophomore-success/" title="FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: LAS Fall 2018 Sophomore Success" rel="bookmark">
						<span class="month">Sep</span>
						<span class="day">01</span>
						<span class="year">2018</span>
					</a></span>


					

					<span class="meta-author"><span>by jvolpe</span></span>

				</div>
                
				<div class="post-contents">
										<h3 class="entry-title">
					<a href="https://advising.uic.edu/for-advisors-info-las-fall-2018-sophomore-success/" title="FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: LAS Fall 2018 Sophomore Success" rel="bookmark">FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: LAS Fall 2018 Sophomore Success</a>
					</h3>
                    					    <div class="post-category">Posted in <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/advising-weekly-updates/">Advising Weekly Updates</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/for-advisors-information/">For Advisors' Information</a></div>
                    					<div class="post-content">
					<p>The LAS Academic Advising Center is excited to inform all campus advisors of our Fall 2018 Sophomore Success advising. In an effort to help our students connect more quickly with their academic departments, or to provide support if they are truly undecided, all LAS sophomores (specifically, students who were new first-year students in Fall 2017) will be required to participate in one of the following in order to register for the Spring 2019 term:</p>
<p>&#8211; Departmental Group Advising<br />
&#8211; Departmental Individual Advising appointment<br />
&#8211; Major Exploration offerings<br />
&#8211; General Individual Advising appointment (if pursuing a “Teaching of” degree or interested in an intercollege transfer out of LAS)</p>
<p>Additional important notes:<br />
&#8211; The Sophomore Success group advising and major exploration offerings schedule is available in the LAS advising portal (student.las.uic.edu) of students for whom it’s required, and takes place during Weeks 4-12. Seats are limited, so students should choose quickly, and reschedule if they’re not able to attend the session for which they have RSVPed.<br />
&#8211; Holds will not be lifted until students have completed one of the above options.<br />
&#8211; Sophomores who are registered for Fall 2018 have already been notified of the Sophomore Success initiative via email from <a href="mailto:LASadvising@uic.edu">LASadvising@uic.edu</a>.</p>
<p>Please contact Katy Schmidt (<a href="mailto:katyk@uic.edu">katyk@uic.edu</a>) if you have any questions. Thank you, in advance, for your support of this effort!</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<br class="clear" />

			</div><!-- end div post -->

		
			<div id="post-3755" class="post-3755 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-advising-weekly-updates category-for-advisors-information">

                                <div class="postmetadata">
					<span class="meta-date"><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/for-advisors-information-fall-2018-placement-testing-deadlines-for-students-to-complete-testing/" title="FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: Fall 2018 Placement Testing deadlines for students to complete testing!" rel="bookmark">
						<span class="month">Sep</span>
						<span class="day">01</span>
						<span class="year">2018</span>
					</a></span>


					

					<span class="meta-author"><span>by jvolpe</span></span>

				</div>
                
				<div class="post-contents">
										<h3 class="entry-title">
					<a href="https://advising.uic.edu/for-advisors-information-fall-2018-placement-testing-deadlines-for-students-to-complete-testing/" title="FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: Fall 2018 Placement Testing deadlines for students to complete testing!" rel="bookmark">FOR ADVISORS&#8217; INFORMATION: Fall 2018 Placement Testing deadlines for students to complete testing!</a>
					</h3>
                    					    <div class="post-category">Posted in <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/advising-weekly-updates/">Advising Weekly Updates</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/for-advisors-information/">For Advisors' Information</a></div>
                    					<div class="post-content">
					<p>The Fall 2018 deadlines for completing a placement test to be able register for a class by the add/drop deadline date (September 7, 2018) are:</p>
<ol>
<li>Chemistry, Physics, French, German, Italian, Latin, Math, Polish, and Russian &#8211; 3:00 PM Wednesday September 5, 2018</li>
</ol>
<ol start="2">
<li>Arabic, Chinese, Computer Science, English, Korean, Japanese, Modern Greek, and Spanish &#8211; 3:00 PM Sunday September 2, 2018</li>
</ol>
<p>Students can take placement tests until Sunday September 9 at 3:00 pm.  Graders have until the end of the day Wednesday September 12, 2018 to finishing grading.  The entire system will go down for the annual upgrade on Thursday September 13, 2018. The system will be back on-line on October 31, 2018.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<br class="clear" />

			</div><!-- end div post -->

		
			<div id="post-3741" class="post-3741 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-advising-weekly-updates category-for-advisors-information category-share-with-students">

                                <div class="postmetadata">
					<span class="meta-date"><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-developmentshare-with-students-weeks-of-welcome-wow-events-until-930/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT/SHARE WITH STUDENTS: Weeks of Welcome (WOW) &#8211; events until 9/30!" rel="bookmark">
						<span class="month">Aug</span>
						<span class="day">26</span>
						<span class="year">2018</span>
					</a></span>


					

					<span class="meta-author"><span>by jvolpe</span></span>

				</div>
                
				<div class="post-contents">
										<h3 class="entry-title">
					<a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-developmentshare-with-students-weeks-of-welcome-wow-events-until-930/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT/SHARE WITH STUDENTS: Weeks of Welcome (WOW) &#8211; events until 9/30!" rel="bookmark">PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT/SHARE WITH STUDENTS: Weeks of Welcome (WOW) &#8211; events until 9/30!</a>
					</h3>
                    					    <div class="post-category">Posted in <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/advising-weekly-updates/">Advising Weekly Updates</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/for-advisors-information/">For Advisors' Information</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/share-with-students/">Share with Students</a></div>
                    					<div class="post-content">
					<p>We’re emailing to let you know about a staff engagement opportunity available the first week of classes. As some of you know, <a href="wow.uic.edu">Weeks of Welcome</a> (WOW) is a campus-wide series of events designed to welcome both new first-year, transfer and graduate students to UIC, as well as to welcome back returning students.  The calendar of events spans the first few weeks from August 22-September 30th.  During these weeks, we want our UIC students to have a sense of belonging and connection to UIC.  It is also a great way to show UIC school spirit and learn about Flames Friday!</p>
<p>Leading up to the first day of classes and through the first week we have <strong>WOW Welcome Tables</strong> throughout different locations on campus. The tables serve as information booths for students to stop by and ask for directions or just to chat about programs offered during Weeks of Welcome.  If you’re available please sign up <a href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1McWSRpR2gSz98gI86Pv-Jqtws7C3Mj7cldbFVtVYjM4/edit#gid=1553936217">HERE</a> for at least a one-hour timeslot. The tables will have WOW handbills and campus maps to help direct students. Once you sign-up you will receive a confirmation email with more details.</p>
<p>Please feel free to share many of our Weeks of Welcome posts directly from our social media.  Both UICLife, UICCSI, and SAB will be promoting various events.  There are a number of events from your colleges, units, and Student Affairs on the Weeks of Welcome website.  Email us with any questions and share with your colleagues.</p>
<p>Thank you for helping get the word out to our UIC students, faculty, staff, and alumni!</p>
<p>Joy &amp; Sladjana</p>
<p><strong>Joy Vergara, M. Ed</strong><strong>, </strong>Executive Director<br />
<strong>Sladjana Grbic,</strong> Assistant Director<br />
Center for Student Involvement (CSI)<br />
University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC)<br />
<a href="mailto:sgrbic2@uic.edu">sgrbic2@uic.edu</a> | 312-413-5076<br />
750 S. Halsted Street, Ste 340<br />
Chicago, IL 60607</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<br class="clear" />

			</div><!-- end div post -->

		
			<div id="post-3716" class="post-3716 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-advising-weekly-updates category-for-advisors-information category-professional-development">

                                <div class="postmetadata">
					<span class="meta-date"><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-development-housing-first-year-student-welcome-dinner-on-827-youre-invited-rsvp/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Housing First-Year Student Welcome Dinner on 8/27 &#8211; YOU&#8217;RE INVITED! RSVP" rel="bookmark">
						<span class="month">Aug</span>
						<span class="day">19</span>
						<span class="year">2018</span>
					</a></span>


					

					<span class="meta-author"><span>by jvolpe</span></span>

				</div>
                
				<div class="post-contents">
										<h3 class="entry-title">
					<a href="https://advising.uic.edu/professional-development-housing-first-year-student-welcome-dinner-on-827-youre-invited-rsvp/" title="PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Housing First-Year Student Welcome Dinner on 8/27 &#8211; YOU&#8217;RE INVITED! RSVP" rel="bookmark">PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT: Housing First-Year Student Welcome Dinner on 8/27 &#8211; YOU&#8217;RE INVITED! RSVP</a>
					</h3>
                    					    <div class="post-category">Posted in <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/advising-weekly-updates/">Advising Weekly Updates</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/for-advisors-information/">For Advisors' Information</a>, <a href="https://advising.uic.edu/category/professional-development/">Professional Development</a></div>
                    					<div class="post-content">
					<p>Join over 1,000 new first-year students as they celebrate their first day on campus!</p>
<p><a href="https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-3719" src="https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="200" srcset="https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-300x200.jpg 300w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-768x512.jpg 768w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-1024x683.jpg 1024w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-150x100.jpg 150w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-200x133.jpg 200w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-250x166.jpg 250w, https://advising.uic.edu/files/2018/08/IMG_5577-1000x667.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" /></a></p>
<p>Housing invites you to join resident students at the First-Year Student Welcome Dinner in the Forum on Wednesday 8/22 at 6pm. After they finish moving in, students will enjoy a casual dinner with faculty, staff, and other new students, and guests like Coach McClain and the Pep Band! Join a table and catch the excitement! Attire is casual, but space is limited, so contact Nick Ardinger at <a href="mailto:ardinger@uic.edu">ardinger@uic.edu</a> ASAP if interested.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
